10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Fellow is best suited for managers, meeting heavy teams, leadership, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Motion, meanwhile, shines for busy professionals, executives, time strapped teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Fellow describes itself as \"AI meeting management platform for agendas, notes, and action items.\" Motion, established in 2019, positions itself as \"AI-powered calendar that automatically schedules tasks and protects focus time.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Motion** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0). However, this does not mean Fellow is a poor choice — far from it. Fellow excels in its own right, particularly for managers and meeting heavy teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value ai automatically schedules your tasks, go with Motion. If excellent meeting note templates matters more to you, Fellow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
